# Circuit Breaker

Circuit breaker patterns for EWM Robotic Platform P0 improvement #17.

## Auto-Apply Triggers
- When implementing P0 #17 (API rate limiting & circuit breaker)
- When protecting SAP bridge from excessive requests
- When adding fault tolerance to Jiizhijia/MiR/Dify API calls
- When implementing graceful degradation patterns
- When creating request queues for failed operations

## Activation Commands
→ "Implement circuit breaker for SAP bridge with 5 failure threshold and 2-min recovery"
→ "Add rate limiting to API endpoints (100 req/min per IP) using Redis sliding window"
→ "Create fallback strategy for Jiizhijia AGV API when circuit breaker opens"
→ "Implement graceful degradation for robot status retrieval with cache fallback"

## EWM Circuit Breakers
- SAP bridge: 5 failures, 120s recovery, 3 successes to close
- Jiizhijia API: 3 failures, 60s recovery (more sensitive)
- Dify AI service: 5 failures, 180s recovery
- Rate limits: SAP 10 req/s, AGV 50 req/s, API 100 req/min per IP
- Fallbacks: Cache, queue, rule-based logic
- Monitoring: Emit metrics, alert on open circuits
